UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. William E. STRAW, Appellee. No. 7653. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 22, 1934. See, also, 62 F.(2d) 757. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Ernest D. Foots, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal. David Spaulding, of West Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRE CHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
